files.title: It's All Over Now, Baby Blue

reviews.review_text: One of the better shows of the year Maybe not as is spectacular as the show two nights later, but I like this one better. Jerry is on fire during much of this seven stop tour. Many red hot jams and his voice, soon to slide, is as good as it gets by 1981. After some problems at the start, Big River, Loser, CC Rider, and Althea are average to good; starting with Deep Elem Blues, through Bertha it's red-hot. Scarlet Fire is average, and the rest all the way to the end is all some of the best playing in '81. The encore is also maybe the best version of Baby Blue (other than 11/8/70, Jerry ever played. It was chosen on the album of Dylan covers, Posters From The Hanging. Don't miss this!
